    "actions_taken": [
      "Onsite investigation initiated",
      "BSEE inspectors conducted investigation on 19-JAN-2023",
      "Contractor will install camera for visual confirmation of grip",
      "Contractor will obtain confirmation from Floorhands before proceeding",
      "Manufacturer to address unintended movement via alarm system"
    ],
    "summary": "On 07-JAN-2023 at 1920 hours, a single joint of 6.625\" drill pipe (60.78 lbs./ft) being laid down using the Pipe Laydown System (PLS) on the drillship Transocean Deepwater Atlas was released and fell 58 feet onto the pipe skate. The PLS failed to fully grip the pipe due to an unknown hydraulic leak affecting the centralizer and gripper arms, with only the roller jaw engaged. The Assistant Driller's view was obstructed by a derrick beam, preventing visual confirmation of proper grip. No injuries were reported as all personnel were in designated safe step back areas.",
    "recommendations": [
      "Install camera for visual confirmation of proper grip on tubulars",
      "Obtain confirmation of proper grip from Floorhands in safe step back area before proceeding",
      "Manufacturer to address unintended movement of PLS via alarm on Assistant Driller's screen"
    ],
    "key_phrases": [
      "hydraulic leak",
      "gripper failure",
      "obstructed view",
      "lack of verification system",
      "no alarm indication",
      "dropped load"
    ]
  },
